# Technical_Art

## 1. Applies when
Games with complex art pipelines, shader development, procedural content, or performance-critical visuals.

## 2. This document owns
Art pipeline design, optimization, and automation.
Shader development and material function libraries.
Procedural content generation (Houdini, geometry scripts, etc.).
LOD systems, mesh optimization, and draw call budgets.
Rigging standards, skeleton compatibility, and animation retargeting.
Visual effects (VFX) technical implementation.
Art performance profiling and budgets.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Visual style and art direction (→ Art_Style_Guide).
Animation style and keyframe specifications (→ Animation_Design).
Rendering pipeline and engine-level graphics (→ Technical_Design).
UI implementation (→ UI_UX_Design).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Art Pipeline & Automation · 2. Shader Development & Material Functions ·
3. Procedural Content Generation · 4. LOD & Mesh Optimization ·
5. Rigging & Animation Retargeting · 6. VFX Technical Implementation ·
7. Art Performance Profiling

## 5. Common boundaries
- Technical_Art owns "how it's built"; Art_Style_Guide owns "how it looks".
- Rigging lives here; animation state machines live in Animation_Design.
- VFX implementation lives here; VFX design direction may live in Art_Style_Guide.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Check cross-references with Art_Style_Guide for visual targets.
- Check cross-references with Technical_Design for rendering constraints.
